1
00:00:10,791 --> 00:00:12,000
[MAKISE gasps]

2
00:00:12,083 --> 00:00:13,375
[OKABE whimpers]

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,250
[sighs] Jeez, thanks for
letting me know you were here.

4
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:23,000
You're going to get arrested
creeping around like that.

5
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:29,583
[faucet squeaks]

6
00:00:32,083 --> 00:00:34,833
Oh, Happy New Year, I guess.

7
00:00:34,916 --> 00:00:37,125
That's the part where
you're supposed to say it back.

8
00:00:37,208 --> 00:00:40,666
Or maybe it's already too late
to wish people Happy New Year?

9
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:43,291
Anyway... I'm
shocked to see you.

10
00:00:43,375 --> 00:00:45,958
You never show
your face these days.

11
00:00:46,041 --> 00:00:47,625
[gasps]

12
00:00:47,708 --> 00:00:50,625
Hey! Can we not
start the year like this?

13
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:56,375
[OKABE whimpers]

14
00:00:56,458 --> 00:01:00,041
[sobbing]

15
00:02:31,958 --> 00:02:33,375
[OKABE]
Apologies.

16
00:02:33,458 --> 00:02:34,708
Don't worry about it.

17
00:02:34,791 --> 00:02:37,000
Happens to me
sometimes, too.

18
00:02:37,083 --> 00:02:38,458
Were you thinking of her?

19
00:02:40,375 --> 00:02:41,916
Mayuri, I mean.

20
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,333
Huh?

21
00:02:43,416 --> 00:02:46,000
I can't come here without
the memories flooding in.

22
00:02:46,083 --> 00:02:48,833
I hear her footsteps,
then the door opens,

23
00:02:48,916 --> 00:02:51,916
and I half expect to hear
her little sing-song greeting.

24
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,333
--[cup clatters]
--[MAKISE gasps]

25
00:02:53,416 --> 00:02:55,000
Okabe?

26
00:02:55,083 --> 00:02:57,916
[OKABE whimpering]

27
00:03:01,625 --> 00:03:03,000
Are you all right?

28
00:03:03,083 --> 00:03:06,250
[OKABE panting]

29
00:03:20,958 --> 00:03:21,875
[gags]

30
00:03:21,958 --> 00:03:23,000
[OKABE retches]

31
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:24,666
[MAKISE gasps]
Okabe?

32
00:03:26,250 --> 00:03:27,541
[OKABE]
How humiliating.

33
00:03:27,625 --> 00:03:28,875
[MAKISE]
Please, it's fine.

34
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:31,500
I really should have known
better. It's too soon.

35
00:03:31,583 --> 00:03:32,583
Now that I think about it,

36
00:03:32,666 --> 00:03:34,500
you haven't even
set foot in this place.

37
00:03:34,583 --> 00:03:36,958
Not once since everything
happened with Mayuri.

38
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:39,833
[OKABE]
Guess not.

39
00:03:39,916 --> 00:03:41,916
You essentially
just disappeared,

40
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,416
not that I blame you.

41
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:45,125
Hashida did, too,

42
00:03:45,208 --> 00:03:47,458
but not on
the same level as you.

43
00:03:48,541 --> 00:03:49,916
[OKABE]
How did this happen?

44
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,791
I'm back in
an alpha world line.

45
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:54,291
[gasps]

46
00:03:56,458 --> 00:03:58,166
Where is the Phone Wave?

47
00:03:58,250 --> 00:04:00,291
Asks the person
who demolished it.

48
00:04:00,375 --> 00:04:01,708
You don't recall?

49
00:04:05,041 --> 00:04:07,583
[MAKISE gasps]

50
00:04:07,666 --> 00:04:10,125
--Okabe?
--Forgive me.

51
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:12,416
I need a little fresh air.

52
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:13,708
Sure.

53
00:04:13,791 --> 00:04:15,291
I understand.

54
00:04:18,416 --> 00:04:19,708
[door latch clacks]

55
00:04:24,166 --> 00:04:27,166
[OKABE] The city and its people
feel exactly the same.

56
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:30,041
To them,
today's just like yesterday.

57
00:04:31,375 --> 00:04:34,583
[OKABE] And yet,
in this alpha world line,

58
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:36,791
life has no meaning.

59
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:38,125
'Cause no matter what I do,

60
00:04:38,208 --> 00:04:41,375
convergence will always
result in Mayuri's death.

61
00:04:41,458 --> 00:04:42,958
I'm powerless.

62
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,750
[DARU] They're taking her
to the hospital now.

63
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:55,500
The paramedics say
it looks like a heart attack.

64
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:59,000
[OKABE] Even if we could escape
the grasp of SERN somehow,

65
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:00,625
as long as I'm
in this world line,

66
00:05:00,708 --> 00:05:04,083
Mayuri's life simply
cannot be saved.

67
00:05:04,166 --> 00:05:06,458
I knew that,
which is why I--

68
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:09,375
[OKABE pants]

69
00:05:09,458 --> 00:05:12,083
How?! How could I
end up back here?

70
00:05:12,166 --> 00:05:15,000
What made
Reading Steiner kick in?

71
00:05:15,083 --> 00:05:16,375
There was no D-mail!

72
00:05:16,458 --> 00:05:19,375
There was no time leaping,
so why?!

73
00:05:19,458 --> 00:05:20,541
[inaudible]

74
00:05:23,208 --> 00:05:24,833
--[DARU] Okarin?
--Huh?

75
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:29,250
[OKABE]
Daru?

76
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:32,041
You in Akiba?
That's a rare sight these days.

77
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:35,541
[FUBUKI]
Welcome to May Queen, meow!

78
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:37,833
Thanks for coming in, Masters!

79
00:05:37,916 --> 00:05:39,666
Daddy's back!

80
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:42,208
Special treat: I brought
Okarin in with me today!

81
00:05:42,291 --> 00:05:43,333
[RUKA gasps]

82
00:05:43,416 --> 00:05:45,125
What? Okabe's here?

83
00:05:45,208 --> 00:05:47,375
-[OKABE] Rukako?
-Kyouma!

84
00:05:47,458 --> 00:05:48,458
[FARIS giggling]

85
00:05:48,541 --> 00:05:50,125
[FARIS]
I've missed you so much, meow!

86
00:05:50,208 --> 00:05:52,166
[OKABE] Has it really been
that long since I came in?

87
00:05:52,250 --> 00:05:54,125
[RUKA]
Yeah, it has.

88
00:05:54,208 --> 00:05:55,208
[DARU]
For a little while there,

89
00:05:55,291 --> 00:05:57,833
I didn't come in
all that much, either.

90
00:05:57,916 --> 00:06:00,000
-[FUBUKI] Excuse me.
-[GROUP] Hmm?

91
00:06:00,083 --> 00:06:01,333
[FUBUKI]
My name's Fubuki.

92
00:06:01,416 --> 00:06:02,833
Glad to finally meet you.

93
00:06:02,916 --> 00:06:04,416
Mayuri and I
were cosplay friends,

94
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:07,708
and I just want you to know
that she meant the world to me.

95
00:06:07,791 --> 00:06:09,333
[FARIS] Fubu-meow
graciously stepped in

96
00:06:09,416 --> 00:06:10,458
to help out at May Queen

97
00:06:10,541 --> 00:06:13,375
after our sweet
Mayushii left us.

98
00:06:13,458 --> 00:06:14,583
[FUBUKI]
It's been hard for me,

99
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:16,083
but I know that Mayuri
would have wanted me

100
00:06:16,166 --> 00:06:17,333
to be around other people

101
00:06:17,416 --> 00:06:19,125
who loved her.

102
00:06:19,208 --> 00:06:21,666
Here's a picture of us
at Summer ComiMa.

103
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:23,666
The outfits she made us
were so cute.

104
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:26,583
We took this picture,
so we could remember it forever.

105
00:06:26,666 --> 00:06:29,458
She was always so energetic.

106
00:06:29,541 --> 00:06:32,125
[voice breaking] And she seemed
healthy, so I was shocked.

107
00:06:32,208 --> 00:06:34,458
One minute she was alive,
and the next--

108
00:06:34,541 --> 00:06:36,916
[crying]

109
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,333
Fubu-meow. Remember what I said?

110
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:42,833
Mayushii would want you to smile
when you remember her, not cry.

111
00:06:42,916 --> 00:06:46,333
Okay? I know it hurts.

112
00:06:46,416 --> 00:06:47,791
[OKABE]
What if...

113
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:52,000
What if there was a world

114
00:06:52,083 --> 00:06:54,416
where Mayuri was still alive?

115
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:56,958
If you knew it existed...

116
00:06:57,041 --> 00:06:58,375
...would it hurt less?

117
00:07:00,375 --> 00:07:01,375
[OKABE]
Daru?

118
00:07:01,458 --> 00:07:03,125
[DARU firmly]
Step outside with me.

119
00:07:03,208 --> 00:07:04,500
[OKABE]
H-Hey!

120
00:07:06,041 --> 00:07:07,583
Poor Okabe.

121
00:07:10,375 --> 00:07:12,208
[OKABE]
What is with you?

122
00:07:12,291 --> 00:07:13,541
[DARU]
There are things you should say,

123
00:07:13,625 --> 00:07:17,000
and things you should
definitely not say!

124
00:07:17,083 --> 00:07:19,875
You want to talk about a world
where Mayuri's alive?

125
00:07:19,958 --> 00:07:21,333
You're the one who
couldn't make the choice

126
00:07:21,416 --> 00:07:24,291
to keep her with us in this one!

127
00:07:24,375 --> 00:07:26,583
We had Echelon's data hacked.

128
00:07:26,666 --> 00:07:28,375
Cracked wide open.

129
00:07:28,458 --> 00:07:30,333
But you
couldn't pull the trigger!

130
00:07:30,416 --> 00:07:34,208
You mean I couldn't
press the "enter" key?

131
00:07:34,291 --> 00:07:35,666
[DARU]
Yeah.

132
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:37,833
And then you wouldn't
shut up about it.

133
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:40,083
You kept saying,
"I'm the one who killed her.

134
00:07:40,166 --> 00:07:42,000
I did it. I killed Mayuri."

135
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:46,041
You made the choice that
effectively ended Mayuri's life.

136
00:07:46,125 --> 00:07:47,416
[DARU]
And then, to top it off,

137
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:50,000
you destroyed the Phone Wave
and Time Leap Machine?

138
00:07:50,083 --> 00:07:51,958
If you knew you were
going to regret it later,

139
00:07:52,041 --> 00:07:54,750
you should have thought
about that and kept it intact!

140
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:57,208
Just like Miss Makise
begged you to.

141
00:07:57,291 --> 00:07:58,375
[OKABE]
Kurisu did?

142
00:07:58,458 --> 00:08:00,625
[DARU] She thought
we had another chance!

143
00:08:00,708 --> 00:08:02,583
We could have
tried it all again!

144
00:08:02,666 --> 00:08:04,916
There must have been
something we hadn't thought of!

145
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,166
[phone buzzes]

146
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:10,791
[MAKISE]
Hello, this is Makise.

147
00:08:10,875 --> 00:08:12,833
Oh, Hashida.
It's been a while.

148
00:08:12,916 --> 00:08:14,250
Happy New Year, by the way.

149
00:08:14,333 --> 00:08:15,875
[DARU]
Yeah, Happy New Year and stuff.

150
00:08:15,958 --> 00:08:17,291
[MAKISE]
This is a surprise.

151
00:08:17,375 --> 00:08:19,833
What's going on?
You practically never call me.

152
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:22,875
I saw Okarin in Akiba.

153
00:08:22,958 --> 00:08:24,375
Oh?

154
00:08:24,458 --> 00:08:26,500
[DARU] I'm guessing he came
to the lab, too, didn't he?

155
00:08:26,583 --> 00:08:29,958
'Course. Did he say
anything strange?

156
00:08:30,041 --> 00:08:31,083
Yeah.

157
00:08:31,166 --> 00:08:33,583
He still isn't over
Mayushii's death.

158
00:08:33,666 --> 00:08:35,833
And then he just started
raving about another world

159
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:37,708
where she could
somehow be alive.

160
00:08:39,291 --> 00:08:41,250
What'd you say?

161
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:42,958
[DARU sighs]
I got pissed.

162
00:08:43,041 --> 00:08:45,000
I-I couldn't believe he'd have
the balls to say all that

163
00:08:45,083 --> 00:08:47,000
after everything that happened.

164
00:08:47,083 --> 00:08:48,333
You don't think he's...?

165
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:56,833
[door clicks]

166
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:59,541
[footsteps running]

167
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:12,208
[footsteps approaching]

168
00:09:18,916 --> 00:09:20,500
[OKABE]
Kurisu?

169
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:22,083
How did you know I was here?

170
00:09:22,166 --> 00:09:23,125
No offense.

171
00:09:23,208 --> 00:09:25,291
You're predictable, so...

172
00:09:25,375 --> 00:09:26,833
That's true.

173
00:09:26,916 --> 00:09:28,750
--[MAKISE] Just kidding.
--Huh?

174
00:09:32,416 --> 00:09:33,458
GPS.

175
00:09:33,541 --> 00:09:35,291
You mean you were tracking me?

176
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:37,000
That confirms my suspicion.

177
00:09:38,708 --> 00:09:40,750
Look, Okabe, be honest.

178
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:43,458
You came from a different
world line, didn't you?

179
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:44,875
[gasps]

180
00:09:54,583 --> 00:09:56,375
You realize that spot
you're occupying

181
00:09:56,458 --> 00:09:59,708
is the place Mayuri
always used to sit, right?

182
00:09:59,791 --> 00:10:01,708
If you were the Okabe
who gave up on her,

183
00:10:01,791 --> 00:10:05,416
you wouldn't ever dream
of sitting in her favorite seat.

184
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:06,958
He never did.

185
00:10:07,041 --> 00:10:08,500
It's how he coped
with the guilt.

186
00:10:10,166 --> 00:10:14,125
Also, you seem to have
no recollection of the GPS.

187
00:10:14,208 --> 00:10:17,125
[OKABE]
You're right. So what's it for?

188
00:10:17,208 --> 00:10:18,583
I won't say.

189
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:26,833
[OKABE]
It's still here?!

190
00:10:26,916 --> 00:10:28,458
[MAKISE]
No, I rebuilt it.

191
00:10:28,541 --> 00:10:30,541
I christened it
"Phone Wave Revised."

192
00:10:30,625 --> 00:10:33,750
Although, you think "reboot"
would be more precise? Huh?

193
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:35,625
[OKABE]
You really remade it?

194
00:10:35,708 --> 00:10:37,208
What for?!

195
00:10:37,291 --> 00:10:39,625
To send a message into the past.

196
00:10:39,708 --> 00:10:41,125
No.

197
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:43,250
In order to change world lines.

198
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:44,750
--[OKABE gasps]
--[MAKISE] Okabe.

199
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:46,083
I want you to use it.

200
00:10:46,166 --> 00:10:48,916
Go back to the world line
you came from.

201
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,791
[OKABE]
What are you...?

202
00:10:50,875 --> 00:10:53,125
In that place,
Mayuri still lives.

203
00:10:53,208 --> 00:10:55,333
Or, rather, in that world line,
you were able

204
00:10:55,416 --> 00:10:57,958
to find the resolve
it took to keep her alive.

205
00:10:58,041 --> 00:10:59,750
[OKABE gasps]

206
00:10:59,833 --> 00:11:01,125
I should have known.

207
00:11:01,208 --> 00:11:03,750
--You see right through me.
--[MAKISE] Naturally.

208
00:11:03,833 --> 00:11:05,375
I've watched you for so long.

209
00:11:05,458 --> 00:11:07,916
No, wait.
I didn't mean in that way.

210
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,000
Well, that, too, but still.

211
00:11:10,083 --> 00:11:11,583
That's not the point.

212
00:11:11,666 --> 00:11:14,875
You're the Okabe Rintaro from
a wholly different world line.

213
00:11:14,958 --> 00:11:17,083
That's all there is to say.

214
00:11:17,166 --> 00:11:18,375
Go back.

215
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:23,833
I did change world lines, yes,

216
00:11:23,916 --> 00:11:26,958
and in the other one,
Mayuri is still alive.

217
00:11:27,041 --> 00:11:28,416
And yet...

218
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:31,375
...that other world where
Mayuri's thriving and happy,

219
00:11:31,458 --> 00:11:33,416
was altered enough
to bring me back to this one,

220
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:35,208
and I've no idea how.

221
00:11:35,291 --> 00:11:36,500
I wish I did.

222
00:11:36,583 --> 00:11:39,500
I wish I could take
responsibility for it.

223
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:41,000
I'm powerless.

224
00:11:41,083 --> 00:11:42,750
I don't know
how I ended up here.

225
00:11:43,875 --> 00:11:47,000
And you, you're not there.

226
00:11:47,083 --> 00:11:49,708
You loved me,
and I tried to save you.

227
00:11:49,791 --> 00:11:52,541
But I failed,
and it cost you your life.

228
00:11:52,625 --> 00:11:53,833
And now...

229
00:11:53,916 --> 00:11:55,583
...you want me to...

230
00:11:55,666 --> 00:11:58,541
You want to make me
kill you all over again?

231
00:11:58,625 --> 00:12:00,250
I can't do it.

232
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:02,041
I don't have the strength.

233
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:10,791
[footsteps]

234
00:12:10,875 --> 00:12:12,041
Hashida?

235
00:12:13,791 --> 00:12:15,000
Where's Okarin?

236
00:12:15,083 --> 00:12:16,916
[MAKISE]
Not sure. He'll be back.

237
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,375
I should have known.
We both should have.

238
00:12:19,458 --> 00:12:21,666
Okabe never could
have let Mayuri go.

239
00:12:24,375 --> 00:12:26,458
Hey, Miss Makise?

240
00:12:26,541 --> 00:12:28,958
No, it's nothing.
Forget about it.

241
00:12:29,041 --> 00:12:34,500
♪

242
00:13:05,958 --> 00:13:10,333
[phone buzzes]

243
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:14,875
[MAKISE]
Have you made up your mind?

244
00:13:14,958 --> 00:13:16,541
[OKABE sighs]

245
00:13:16,625 --> 00:13:18,833
No, of course you haven't.

246
00:13:18,916 --> 00:13:21,625
Well, the trains are running,
are they not?

247
00:13:21,708 --> 00:13:24,958
Meet me in an hour at Akihabara
station, if you would.

248
00:13:25,041 --> 00:13:26,291
What's up?

249
00:13:26,375 --> 00:13:28,208
[MAKISE] There's something
I think you need to see.

250
00:13:32,875 --> 00:13:35,375
[MAKISE] You're hard
to spot without the lab coat.

251
00:13:35,458 --> 00:13:37,791
What is this?
Where are we going?

252
00:13:37,875 --> 00:13:39,625
You'll know
when we arrive there.

253
00:13:47,458 --> 00:13:49,250
--What is it?
--Oh.

254
00:13:49,333 --> 00:13:51,458
I was just noting that
we've never traveled together.

255
00:13:51,541 --> 00:13:52,500
Not like this.

256
00:13:52,583 --> 00:13:54,000
Well, you better stop ogling me

257
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:56,041
or I shall be forced
to report you.

258
00:13:56,125 --> 00:13:57,291
But I'm blameless.

259
00:13:57,375 --> 00:13:59,083
The law is quite clear
on this matter.

260
00:13:59,166 --> 00:14:02,250
An unwanted gaze
is sexual harassment.

261
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:03,375
[laughs softly]

262
00:14:03,458 --> 00:14:05,541
Amadeus has got nothing
on the real you.

263
00:14:05,625 --> 00:14:07,166
[MAKISE gasps]
Amadeus?

264
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:09,041
[OKABE] You know,
the artificial intelligence.

265
00:14:09,125 --> 00:14:11,125
How did you
even hear about that?

266
00:14:11,208 --> 00:14:12,625
I'm sure I never told you!

267
00:14:12,708 --> 00:14:15,291
[OKABE] You're right. Hiyajo
and Professor Leskinen did.

268
00:14:15,375 --> 00:14:17,833
[MAKISE gasps]
You've met Miss Maho?!

269
00:14:17,916 --> 00:14:20,166
What kind of world line
would allow for that to happen?

270
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:21,208
[OKABE]
What're you so angry about?

271
00:14:21,291 --> 00:14:23,083
[MAKISE]
Who says I'm angry?!

272
00:14:27,458 --> 00:14:28,666
[OKABE]
Next thing we knew,

273
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:30,958
she wasn't able to access
Amadeus at all.

274
00:14:31,041 --> 00:14:32,125
[MAKISE]
Hmm.

275
00:14:32,208 --> 00:14:33,583
What happened to it
in this world line?

276
00:14:33,666 --> 00:14:34,958
I don't know.

277
00:14:35,041 --> 00:14:36,833
From a purely
logical perspective,

278
00:14:36,916 --> 00:14:38,125
I can't imagine
an AI could have

279
00:14:38,208 --> 00:14:40,250
much to do
with a world line change.

280
00:14:40,333 --> 00:14:41,541
It doesn't make sense.

281
00:14:41,625 --> 00:14:43,166
What then? Fluke?

282
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:44,708
Well, all of my memories
are contained

283
00:14:44,791 --> 00:14:46,833
within the program's database.

284
00:14:46,916 --> 00:14:48,916
So, it follows that
my time machine concept

285
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,291
would be stored therein,
as well.

286
00:14:50,375 --> 00:14:52,041
-[OKABE] Wait, it would?
-[MAKISE] In theory.

287
00:14:52,125 --> 00:14:54,708
Although I still denied their
plausibility at that point.

288
00:14:54,791 --> 00:14:56,791
No, time machines
aren't possible.

289
00:14:56,875 --> 00:14:58,375
However...

290
00:14:58,458 --> 00:15:01,750
...that isn't to say that time
travel is altogether impossible.

291
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:05,333
[OKABE] Amadeus Kurisu
gave me a very different answer.

292
00:15:05,416 --> 00:15:07,500
Look, please,
I just want you to read this.

293
00:15:07,583 --> 00:15:09,208
'Kay, Dad?

294
00:15:09,291 --> 00:15:10,583
Hold on, excuse me?

295
00:15:10,666 --> 00:15:12,458
That's called stealing,
you know!

296
00:15:12,541 --> 00:15:14,541
--[MAKISE] Okabe?
--[OKABE gasps]

297
00:15:14,625 --> 00:15:17,375
[OKABE stammers]
I'm all right.

298
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,041
I admit, I struggle
to wrap my head around

299
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:21,166
your alleged friendship
with Miss Maho.

300
00:15:21,250 --> 00:15:23,208
I bumped into her at a seminar.

301
00:15:23,291 --> 00:15:24,541
I don't suppose
I have to tell you

302
00:15:24,625 --> 00:15:27,208
just how coarse and stubborn
Hiyajo can be.

303
00:15:27,291 --> 00:15:29,458
Ungainly, too.

304
00:15:29,541 --> 00:15:31,833
I'm well-acquainted
with those qualities.

305
00:15:31,916 --> 00:15:34,750
So, I assume you were
her feisty side-kick, then?

306
00:15:34,833 --> 00:15:36,041
How rude.

307
00:15:36,125 --> 00:15:38,458
I was anything but feisty
when it came to her.

308
00:15:38,541 --> 00:15:40,875
I'd go so far as to
call myself courteous.

309
00:15:40,958 --> 00:15:42,083
Maho adored me.

310
00:15:42,166 --> 00:15:43,541
[OKABE]
Hmph.

311
00:15:43,625 --> 00:15:44,791
[gasps]

312
00:15:51,833 --> 00:15:53,666
[OKABE whimpers]

313
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:00,416
[whimpers]

314
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:12,541
[MAKISE] The others
must be visiting, too.

315
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:16,708
You were a wreck
after Mayuri died.

316
00:16:16,791 --> 00:16:18,708
We were all very
concerned about you.

317
00:16:19,875 --> 00:16:21,000
You stopped going to the lab,

318
00:16:21,083 --> 00:16:22,916
you dropped out of college,

319
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:26,583
and you just stood here,
every day, sun up to sun down.

320
00:16:26,666 --> 00:16:28,041
It was like...

321
00:16:28,125 --> 00:16:29,500
...you were waiting

322
00:16:29,583 --> 00:16:32,250
for someone to take you
to the other side.

323
00:16:36,041 --> 00:16:37,208
[MAKISE] And there was
nothing I could do

324
00:16:37,291 --> 00:16:39,500
to help or to make it better.

325
00:16:39,583 --> 00:16:41,083
After all...

326
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:43,333
...I was the reason
that you didn't save her.

327
00:16:43,416 --> 00:16:44,791
Kurisu...

328
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:47,250
[MAKISE]
Anyway, that's all over.

329
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:50,958
[MAKISE] It ends now,
because it has to.

330
00:16:51,041 --> 00:16:54,291
If not, you'll live the rest of
your life crushed by the guilt.

331
00:16:55,166 --> 00:16:56,583
You're mistaken.

332
00:16:56,666 --> 00:16:59,958
Even if I did go back
to a beta world line...

333
00:17:00,041 --> 00:17:02,458
...I'm crushed
by guilt there, too.

334
00:17:02,541 --> 00:17:04,541
The feeling never leaves me,
and you're dead!

335
00:17:04,625 --> 00:17:07,166
Get ahold of yourself,
Okabe Rintaro!

336
00:17:10,916 --> 00:17:12,875
Please stop making that face.

337
00:17:14,041 --> 00:17:16,208
[MAKISE] If Hououin Kyouma
is still in there somewhere,

338
00:17:16,291 --> 00:17:19,166
then find him. Be brash
and indomitable again!

339
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:21,250
That was an act.
A dumb facade.

340
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:22,625
A lie!

341
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:24,000
It was just something
I used to do

342
00:17:24,083 --> 00:17:26,708
because it always
made Mayuri happy.

343
00:17:26,791 --> 00:17:30,375
And it worked. You never had
any trouble making her smile.

344
00:17:30,458 --> 00:17:32,166
That's all that matters.

345
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:34,916
In the beta world line,
she is happy.

346
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,708
Your choice was based
on what you knew then--

347
00:17:36,791 --> 00:17:38,125
It wasn't wrong.

348
00:17:38,208 --> 00:17:40,833
This world line shouldn't
exist in the first place.

349
00:17:40,916 --> 00:17:42,791
I shouldn't be here.

350
00:17:42,875 --> 00:17:45,041
--This world is only a dream.
--[OKABE sobbing]

351
00:17:45,125 --> 00:17:46,625
A bleak fantasy.

352
00:17:46,708 --> 00:17:49,916
That's why you've got
to go back, Okabe.

353
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,083
It's a dream.

354
00:17:51,166 --> 00:17:53,291
--And you have to wake up.
--A dream?

355
00:17:53,375 --> 00:17:54,666
[MAKISE]
Yes.

356
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:58,083
[OKABE gasps]

357
00:17:58,166 --> 00:18:03,666
♪

358
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:45,291
[MAKISE] We should
head back to the lab now.

359
00:18:49,458 --> 00:18:50,416
[keyboard clacking]

360
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:51,708
[MAKISE]
Before you send the message,

361
00:18:51,791 --> 00:18:53,666
I need you to make me a promise.

362
00:18:53,750 --> 00:18:54,916
[OKABE]
What's that?

363
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,291
[MAKISE]
When you get back,

364
00:18:56,375 --> 00:18:58,041
I want you to forget
all about me.

365
00:18:58,125 --> 00:18:59,458
[OKABE]
I can't do that.

366
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:00,916
There's no way.

367
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,750
[MAKISE]
Then just promise me you'll try.

368
00:19:02,833 --> 00:19:06,000
Even if it's not possible.

369
00:19:06,083 --> 00:19:07,500
Sentiment aside,

370
00:19:07,583 --> 00:19:10,125
Amadeus could be key.

371
00:19:10,208 --> 00:19:11,458
I don't have
the slightest inkling

372
00:19:11,541 --> 00:19:13,541
of what caused
your world line to change.

373
00:19:13,625 --> 00:19:17,541
However, time travel had to
have been involved somehow.

374
00:19:17,625 --> 00:19:18,958
[OKABE]
But the Phone Wave was--

375
00:19:19,041 --> 00:19:21,666
I can't make any claims
about myself in your world line.

376
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:24,541
But in this one, there's
no question, whatsoever,

377
00:19:24,625 --> 00:19:28,125
that I only completed my time
machine theory after I met you.

378
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:30,875
I can't guarantee
it won't happen again.

379
00:19:30,958 --> 00:19:32,375
It would behoove you, 

380
00:19:32,458 --> 00:19:34,750
not to interact with Amadeus
too much when you get there.

381
00:19:37,708 --> 00:19:38,958
[OKABE sighs]

382
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:41,833
This is a pinky promise.

383
00:19:41,916 --> 00:19:43,750
Break it
and I'll stab an electrode

384
00:19:43,833 --> 00:19:46,666
into your hippocampus!

385
00:19:46,750 --> 00:19:48,666
'Cause it's a pinky promise!

386
00:19:50,416 --> 00:19:52,666
--That was really lame.
--Oh, shut up.

387
00:20:08,416 --> 00:20:09,958
--[MAKISE] Hey.
--Huh?

388
00:20:10,041 --> 00:20:11,458
[MAKISE]
Do you remember...

389
00:20:11,541 --> 00:20:13,791
...what happened
the day we first met?

390
00:20:13,875 --> 00:20:15,333
You were pulling
and pawing at my clothes

391
00:20:15,416 --> 00:20:17,416
like a crazy person.

392
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,791
I was sure you were
some kind of deranged pervert.

393
00:20:21,166 --> 00:20:22,500
[OKABE]
Makes sense.

394
00:20:22,583 --> 00:20:25,708
From her perspective,
that is the first time we met.

395
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:28,041
And yet, from mine, she was...

396
00:20:29,958 --> 00:20:31,291
Wait!

397
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:35,500
[inaudible]

398
00:20:35,583 --> 00:20:37,666
[keyboard clacking]

399
00:20:38,791 --> 00:20:40,541
Everything's ready now.

400
00:20:40,625 --> 00:20:42,500
All you have to do
is send that message,

401
00:20:42,583 --> 00:20:44,833
and then you'll return
to the world line you came from.

402
00:20:45,791 --> 00:20:48,333
[whirring]

403
00:20:52,916 --> 00:20:53,833
Okabe?

404
00:20:53,916 --> 00:20:55,458
Sorry. Yeah.

405
00:21:00,958 --> 00:21:02,375
[OKABE]
If I send this...

406
00:21:02,458 --> 00:21:04,541
...I'll be sent back,
and everything reverts.

407
00:21:05,416 --> 00:21:07,666
[OKABE]
A world where Mayuri lives.

408
00:21:07,750 --> 00:21:10,000
A world where
I don't have to lose her.

409
00:21:10,083 --> 00:21:12,916
But instead,
I lose the woman in front of me.

410
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,958
Kurisu will be gone,
because I'll have killed her.

411
00:21:16,041 --> 00:21:18,000
The one I love.

412
00:21:18,083 --> 00:21:19,333
My most precious--

413
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:23,916
[gasps]

414
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:30,916
Okabe?

415
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:38,541
♪

416
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:10,041
[MAKISE]
I'm so grateful that I met you.

417
00:22:12,166 --> 00:22:13,416
[OKABE]
Kurisu?

418
00:22:17,875 --> 00:22:19,250
[groaning]

419
00:22:26,458 --> 00:22:29,208
[MAKISE panting]

420
00:22:43,583 --> 00:22:48,583
[MAKISE panting]

421
00:22:51,166 --> 00:22:53,708
[inaudible]

422
00:23:03,208 --> 00:23:06,791
[inaudible]

423
00:23:06,875 --> 00:23:08,625
[panting]

424
00:23:08,708 --> 00:23:10,833
[inaudible]

425
00:23:19,750 --> 00:23:22,041
[panting]

426
00:23:24,250 --> 00:23:25,583
[gasps]

427
00:23:30,208 --> 00:23:31,291
[gasps]

428
00:23:33,458 --> 00:23:34,750
[MAKISE]
Okabe!

429
00:23:36,541 --> 00:23:38,791
[MAKISE]
You should know by now!

430
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:40,250
I'm in love with--

